<paragraph id="8B90152CEF50A2118BD5FD4DFE91FB2F" blockId="39.[151,1437,505,1970]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">
Male imago. Length (mm): body, 7.8–8.5; foreleg, 3.1–3.3; fore wing, 6.9–8.0; hind wing, 3.5–3.6; cerci, 21.0–22.5. General coloration whitish yellow with grayish brown marks (
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF50A21188FFFD69FBDAFD73" box="[1005,1106,685,710]" captionStart="FIGURES 176 – 177" captionStartId="46.[151,264,887,910]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,161,861]" captionTargetId="figure@46.[150,1436,157,865]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 176 – 177. Male imago, general view, dorsal: 176, C. cotaxe sp. nov.; 177, C. litaninensis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838484/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Fig. 176</figureCitation>
). Head whitish, shaded with black among ocelli; occiput pale, not shaded. Antenna whitish, shaded with gray. Thorax (
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF50A2118FA0FD15FA9FFD5F" box="[1202,1303,721,746]" captionStart="FIGURES 176 – 177" captionStartId="46.[151,264,887,910]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,161,861]" captionTargetId="figure@46.[150,1436,157,865]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 176 – 177. Male imago, general view, dorsal: 176, C. cotaxe sp. nov.; 177, C. litaninensis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838484/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Fig. 176</figureCitation>
). Pronotum translucent, shaded with grayish brown anterolaterally. Mesonotum yellowish white, shaded with grayish brown dorsally, mainly on carinae, 
<collectionCode id="ED3E8DE9EF50A2118AC3FCDEFD88FC87" box="[465,512,794,818]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15543" name="Parasitic Seed Plants" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">PSP</collectionCode>
and area between 
<collectionCode id="ED3E8DE9EF50A21189DCFCDEFD75FC87" box="[718,765,794,818]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15543" name="Parasitic Seed Plants" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">PSP</collectionCode>
. Metanotum yellowish white, shaded with grayish brown on submedian mark. Pleura and sterna shaded more widely with grayish brown, darker on carinae and mesofurcasternum. Legs yellowish white, shaded with gray. Wings. Membrane translucent with light brownish veins, darker near base and fore margin. Abdomen whitish translucent, shaded with grayish brown dorsally, darker toward rear segments (
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF50A2118A86FC6DFE7EFC77" box="[404,502,937,962]" captionStart="FIGURES 176 – 177" captionStartId="46.[151,264,887,910]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,161,861]" captionTargetId="figure@46.[150,1436,157,865]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 176 – 177. Male imago, general view, dorsal: 176, C. cotaxe sp. nov.; 177, C. litaninensis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838484/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Fig. 176</figureCitation>
); medial area of all nota pale, not strongly shaded. Sterna shaded almost completely with grayish brown. Genitalia translucent yellowish white, hind margin of sternum IX straight (
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF50A2118FDBFC09FAA4FC53" box="[1225,1324,973,998]" captionStart="FIGURES 138 – 145" captionStartId="38.[151,264,1925,1948]" captionTargetBox="[283,1282,265,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[277,1285,265,1880]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 138 – 145. C. segnis, holotype male imago: 138, genitalia, v. v.; 139, penes, v. v. Campsurus cotaxe sp. nov.: 140, genitalia, v. v.; 141, pedestal, v. v.; 142, penes, v. v.; 143, penes, l. v.; 144, female sternum VIII with detail of socket. C. amapaensis: 145, partial view of female sternum VIII with detail of socket." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838472/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Fig. 140</figureCitation>
); pedestal bases distinctly separated in middle, pedestal with conical parastylus (p in 
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF50A21188E4FC35FB1CFBBF" box="[1014,1172,1009,1034]" captionStart="FIGURES 138 – 145" captionStartId="38.[151,264,1925,1948]" captionTargetBox="[283,1282,265,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[277,1285,265,1880]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 138 – 145. C. segnis, holotype male imago: 138, genitalia, v. v.; 139, penes, v. v. Campsurus cotaxe sp. nov.: 140, genitalia, v. v.; 141, pedestal, v. v.; 142, penes, v. v.; 143, penes, l. v.; 144, female sternum VIII with detail of socket. C. amapaensis: 145, partial view of female sternum VIII with detail of socket." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838472/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Fig. 140, 141</figureCitation>
), subequal in length to main body of pedestal, inner corner also projected but slightly (ic in 
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF50A21188BBFBD1FB84FB9B" box="[937,1036,1045,1070]" captionStart="FIGURES 138 – 145" captionStartId="38.[151,264,1925,1948]" captionTargetBox="[283,1282,265,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[277,1285,265,1880]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 138 – 145. C. segnis, holotype male imago: 138, genitalia, v. v.; 139, penes, v. v. Campsurus cotaxe sp. nov.: 140, genitalia, v. v.; 141, pedestal, v. v.; 142, penes, v. v.; 143, penes, l. v.; 144, female sternum VIII with detail of socket. C. amapaensis: 145, partial view of female sternum VIII with detail of socket." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838472/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Fig. 140</figureCitation>
); penes base well developed (bp in 
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF50A2118B85FBFDFF72FBE7" box="[151,250,1081,1106]" captionStart="FIGURES 138 – 145" captionStartId="38.[151,264,1925,1948]" captionTargetBox="[283,1282,265,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[277,1285,265,1880]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 138 – 145. C. segnis, holotype male imago: 138, genitalia, v. v.; 139, penes, v. v. Campsurus cotaxe sp. nov.: 140, genitalia, v. v.; 141, pedestal, v. v.; 142, penes, v. v.; 143, penes, l. v.; 144, female sternum VIII with detail of socket. C. amapaensis: 145, partial view of female sternum VIII with detail of socket." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838472/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Fig. 140</figureCitation>
); main lobe of penes yellowish translucent, long and cylindrical, curved ventromedially (ml in 
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF50A2118E24FBFDFF75FBC3" captionStart="FIGURES 138 – 145" captionStartId="38.[151,264,1925,1948]" captionTargetBox="[283,1282,265,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[277,1285,265,1880]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 138 – 145. C. segnis, holotype male imago: 138, genitalia, v. v.; 139, penes, v. v. Campsurus cotaxe sp. nov.: 140, genitalia, v. v.; 141, pedestal, v. v.; 142, penes, v. v.; 143, penes, l. v.; 144, female sternum VIII with detail of socket. C. amapaensis: 145, partial view of female sternum VIII with detail of socket." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838472/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Fig. 140, 142–143</figureCitation>
); secondary lobe of penes whitish, shorter, cylindrical (sl in 
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF50A21188B2FB99FBF9FBC3" box="[928,1137,1117,1142]" captionStart="FIGURES 138 – 145" captionStartId="38.[151,264,1925,1948]" captionTargetBox="[283,1282,265,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[277,1285,265,1880]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 138 – 145. C. segnis, holotype male imago: 138, genitalia, v. v.; 139, penes, v. v. Campsurus cotaxe sp. nov.: 140, genitalia, v. v.; 141, pedestal, v. v.; 142, penes, v. v.; 143, penes, l. v.; 144, female sternum VIII with detail of socket. C. amapaensis: 145, partial view of female sternum VIII with detail of socket." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838472/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Fig. 140, 142–143</figureCitation>
). Caudal filaments whitish translucent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B90152CEF50A2118BD5FB61FE68FA9F" blockId="39.[151,1437,505,1970]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">
Female imago. Length (mm): body, 9.5–11.2; foreleg reduced to coxa and trochanter; fore wing, 9.6–10.5; hind wing, 3.7–4.3; cerci, 3.0. Color pattern similar to male, except head with larger pale area on occiput, and abdominal sterna with paler medial area. Abdominal sternum VIII with small, paired, anteromedian, V-shaped sockets; furrow relatively narrow (
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF50A2118A74FAD5FE5BFA9F" box="[358,467,1297,1322]" captionStart="FIGURES 138 – 145" captionStartId="38.[151,264,1925,1948]" captionTargetBox="[283,1282,265,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[277,1285,265,1880]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 138 – 145. C. segnis, holotype male imago: 138, genitalia, v. v.; 139, penes, v. v. Campsurus cotaxe sp. nov.: 140, genitalia, v. v.; 141, pedestal, v. v.; 142, penes, v. v.; 143, penes, l. v.; 144, female sternum VIII with detail of socket. C. amapaensis: 145, partial view of female sternum VIII with detail of socket." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838472/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Figs. 144</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B90152CEF50A2118BD5FAF2FD90FAC7" blockId="39.[151,1437,505,1970]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Egg. Length, 330–350 µm; width, 265–275 µm. Yellowish; no polar cap; with small, circular, amorphous, adhesive structure on convex side.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33546A7EF50A2118BD5FAB9FB2CFA23" box="[199,1188,1405,1430]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B90152CEF50A2118BD5FAB9FB2CFA23" blockId="39.[151,1437,505,1970]" box="[199,1188,1405,1430]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">
<emphasis id="B95BC93EEF50A2118BD5FAB9FEC6FA23" bold="true" box="[199,334,1405,1430]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name, a noun in apposition, refers to the 
<typeStatus id="5494AB8EEF50A2118842FABAFC08FA23" box="[848,896,1406,1430]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">type</typeStatus>
locality, the river 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F6EAFEF50A2118F5FFABAFB28FA23" authority="Molineri &amp; Salles, 2017" authorityName="Molineri &amp; Salles" authorityYear="2017" box="[1101,1184,1406,1430]" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Campsurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="351" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cotaxe" status="sp. nov.">Cotaxé</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33546A7EF50A2118BD5FA65FD6BFA0F" box="[199,739,1441,1466]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B90152CEF50A2118BD5FA65FD6BFA0F" blockId="39.[151,1437,505,1970]" box="[199,739,1441,1466]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">
<emphasis id="B95BC93EEF50A2118BD5FA65FED1FA0F" bold="true" box="[199,345,1441,1466]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="131409A9EF50A2118A7AFA65FE42FA0F" box="[360,458,1441,1466]" captionStart="FIGURES 181" captionStartId="51.[151,264,1640,1663]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,195,1619]" captionTargetId="figure@51.[150,1436,195,1619]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="FIGURES 181. Distribution maps." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838492/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Fig. 181</figureCitation>
